notes:
Runtime: qmd needs Node>=22/Bun; rqmd (https://github.com/stn/rqmd) is a native Rust port — same pipeline (SQLite FTS5 BM25 + vectors + RRF fusion + Qwen3 reranker, GGUF models via llama.cpp, tree-sitter chunking, MCP server) but EARLY STAGE (1 star, 82 commits, no releases as of 2026-07-06).

Expanded decision space (per Ihor 2026-07-06):
(a) documentation-only companion — recommend qmd alongside wikid, fully composable (original lean);
(b) embed rqmd — being Rust it could vendor into wikid as an optional cargo feature ('wikid search --semantic'), keeping core dependency-light via feature gate; risk: rqmd maturity, ~2GB model downloads, and it's a CLI not a library so embedding means depending on unstable internals;
(c) semantic search as a PAID feature once wikid goes cloud — wikid-server hosts the index + models, local CLI stays free/structural, semantic endpoints are the monetization surface. (b) and (c) compose: rqmd-in-server could power the paid tier.

Evaluation should now also assess rqmd code quality/embeddability and sketch the cloud pricing surface, not just qmd search quality.
